&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Brainlabs is the media agency built to answer one question: what&#39;s actually driving profit? Founded in 2012 by Daniel Gilbert, we were built by engineers before we were a media agency. Today, 1,000+ Brainlabbers across five continents use our proprietary agents, built on 32 media tools and over 2,500 logged experiments, to help brands connect every channel they plan and buy to one thing: the bottom line.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As the Associate Director, BI, you will lead our most advanced reporting and dashboarding work for clients, setting the standard for how Brainlabs turns data into business decisions. You are accountable for the quality, accuracy, and continuous improvement of our intelligence solutions across your client portfolio, with Claude embedded throughout how we build and deliver them. Working across client teams and in close partnership with the wider Data practice, you will own complex BI projects end-to-end, building solutions that speak as clearly to a Head of Marketing as they do to an analyst.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Client BI Projects: &lt;/strong&gt;You own end-to-end delivery of advanced reporting and dashboarding projects using Funnel, BigQuery, and Looker Studio, ensuring every solution is accurate, scalable, and tied directly to each client’s business objectives rather than just their data requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Continuous Improvement: &lt;/strong&gt;You proactively identify gaps in our dashboarding solutions, implement enhancements, and document best practice so improvements compound across the whole BI team rather than staying locked in a single project.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply Claude Across BI Workflows: &lt;/strong&gt;You build and maintain a clear, demonstrable track record of AI adoption in the reporting process, using Claude to expand what our BI solutions can do and making it a standard part of how the team works rather than an occasional experiment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own Senior Client Relationships: &lt;/strong&gt;You are the primary BI point of contact for senior client stakeholders, including Heads of Marketing, presenting complex data stories confidently and designing outputs that work at every level of the client organisation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support Practice Growth: &lt;/strong&gt;You contribute beyond your client portfolio through new business pitches, internal knowledge sharing, and developing Brainlabs’ BI proposition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Technically Advanced BI Practitioner: &lt;/strong&gt;You are highly proficient in Funnel, BigQuery, and Looker Studio, with hands-on experience building intelligence solutions in-house or at another agency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An AI Innovator: &lt;/strong&gt;You have demonstrable experience using Claude to expand reporting capabilities, and you are excited by the opportunity to push that further across a varied client portfolio.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Multi-Level Communicator: &lt;/strong&gt;You build dashboards that serve every audience, from operational teams digging into the detail to Heads of Marketing making strategic calls, and you present confidently to both.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Commercial Thinker: &lt;/strong&gt;You connect BI work to client value and commercial outcomes, and contribute meaningfully to new business conversations when called on.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Quality-First Operator: &lt;/strong&gt;You hold yourself to rigorous standards on data accuracy, documentation, and reliability, and you have built systems to make that consistent rather than just personal.&lt;/li&gt;
