&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So, tell me about the company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brainlabs is culture-first. You’ve probably heard other companies describe themselves as people, clients, or profit first – but we see people, clients and profit as the building blocks of our ecosystem. Culture powers all three and we know that when the ecosystem is balanced, we all win! That&#39;s why the culture we cultivate is a culture of winning together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To learn more about what it’s like to be a Brainlabber, check out our&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.brainlabsdigital.com/the-brainlabs-culture-code/&quot;&gt; culture code.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and own the data engineering capability roadmap for NAMER, setting standards for how pipelines are designed, maintained, and scaled across the practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and develop a team of data engineers, providing technical direction, career development support, and hands-on guidance on complex problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect scalable, production-grade data solutions on GCP, covering the full stack from ingestion and transformation through to warehousing and serving layers in BigQuery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the quality bar for data engineering output across the team, including pipeline reliability, query performance, data quality frameworks, and documentation standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Data Science, Digital Analytics, and client teams to scope and deliver integrated data solutions, translating complex business requirements into sound technical architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the data engineering practice in client conversations and new business contexts, communicating technical approaches clearly to non-technical stakeholders and contributing to proposals and SOW scoping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive adoption of engineering best practices across the team, including CI/CD, version control, infrastructure-as-code, data governance, and security on GCP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and introduce new tool

